        <p>
            <term>Key Takeaway</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            Did you know one of the real life applications of angles is in <em>Carpentary?</em> 
        </p>

        <p>
            For example, when carpenters are making a chair, 
            they use angles to cut the wood so that the legs of the chair slants at the desired angle thereby creating a stable and beautiful designs.  
        </p>

        <p>   
            
            They typically use a combination of measuring tools, like a protractor and a combination square, to mark the angles on the wood before cutting, often aiming for a slight outward slant on the legs for stability and comfort
        </p>
